Based on last year's accounts, Rangers would have to pay £62.1m if they are promoted because their £65.4m losses were so far in excess of the £8m allowed by the Football League.

Should Redknapp's side stay in the Championship, however, they would be subjected to a transfer embargo.

QPR have tried to reduce their wage bill by selling high-earners such as Christopher Samba and sending the likes of Loic Remy and Adel Taarabt out on loan.

